{
  "answer": "**The work is *Traité de Législation: VOL II* by Charles Comte, Chapter 2 (\"Of the limits placed by nature on the perfection of human faculties\").**[^1]\n\nThis chapter argues that European colonization in America, southern Asia, \"some of the islands of the great Ocean,\" and the south and west of Africa has introduced \"a kind of aristocracy of which we had no idea, **the aristocracy of species**,\" which differs from prior aristocracies based on rank within the same species, and that this \"new combination will considerably influence the existence of the American republics.\"[^1]\n\n[^1]: Charles Comte, *Traité de Législation: VOL II*, [paragraph](/works/charles-comte-traite-de-legislation-vol-ii-20331d/02-des-limites-mises-par-la-nature-au-perfectionnemen/translation/#p-44e2ce).",
